<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<p><strong>How much does SEO cost for an auto repair shop?</strong></p>
<p>Most SEO agencies charge $1,500 to $3,000 per month for local SEO services. Freelancers charge $500 to $1,500. Automated services like Stacc start at $99 per month for 30 blog posts and $49 per month for local SEO and GBP management. The right budget depends on your market competition and how fast you want results.</p>
<p><strong>How long does it take for auto repair SEO to show results?</strong></p>
<p>Expect initial keyword movement within 60 to 90 days. Meaningful traffic and call increases typically appear at the 4 to 6 month mark. Competitive markets may take longer. Consistency matters more than speed. Shops that publish content and manage reviews weekly see faster results than those who make changes once and wait.</p>
<p><strong>Do auto repair shops really need a blog?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Blog content targets hundreds of keywords that your service pages cannot. Posts about repair costs, maintenance tips, and seasonal guides bring potential customers to your website months before they need a repair. That early visibility builds trust and brand familiarity. Shops publishing 4 or more posts per month consistently outrank competitors with static websites.</p>
<p><strong>What is the most important ranking factor for auto repair local SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Google Business Profile completeness and review signals are the two strongest factors. A fully optimized GBP with 100+ recent reviews, accurate categories, weekly posts, and consistent NAP information across citations gives you the strongest local ranking foundation. On-page content and backlinks matter too, but GBP and reviews drive Map Pack results.</p>
<p><strong>Can I do auto repair SEO myself or do I need to hire someone?</strong></p>
<p>You can handle the basics yourself. Claiming and optimizing your GBP, asking for reviews, and updating your website with service pages are all doable without technical expertise. Content creation and ongoing optimization take more time. Most shop owners find that spending 5 to 10 hours per week on SEO is not realistic alongside running a business. That is where automated services or agencies fill the gap.</p>
<p><strong>How do I rank in the Google Map Pack for auto repair searches?</strong></p>
<p>The Map Pack shows the top 3 local results for searches with local intent. To rank there, focus on 3 things: a fully optimized Google Business Profile, a strong review profile with recent positive reviews, and consistent citations across directories. Proximity to the searcher also matters, and you cannot control that. Focus on the factors you can influence.</p>
